gomodel:SYNGO_1020  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use shRNA to knockdown (KD) AP-2 mu2 (gene AP2M1) in cultured rat hippocampal neurons. In figure 2B they use high intensity stimulation to load the neurons with FM4-64 (which is established to enter in synaptic vesicles (SVs). They wash and then stimulate exocytosis to destain the neurons (as the SVs undergo exocytosis, the FM4-64 dye is release into the culture media and looses fluorescence). Destaining in the KD is ~30% of that in control indicating a large decrease in the pool of recycling SVs.\n\nIn figure 3 they examine the rates of endocytosis of 4 major SV proteins tagged with pHlourin. They stimulate exocytosis and then examine endocytosis of SVs post-stimulation. The rates of all 4 proteins are strongly decreased.\n\nIn figure 4 they examine the rate of endocytosis of vGlutpHlourin during intense stimulation and measure a dramatic reduction.\n\nIt is important to note, knockdown of AP-2 mu2 in this manuscript leads to loss of AP-2 alpha. Thus, it is not possible to distinguish between the function of these two proteins as they are obligate heterodimers.. Experimental description: From materials and methods, \"Hippocampal CA3-CA1 regions were dissected from 1- to 3-d-old Sprague Dawley rats...\"\n\n\"shRNA and shRNA-resistant μ2 plasmids. Synthetic oligonucleotides (60-mers) containing the rat μ2 subunit cDNA target sequences (GTGGATGCCTTTCGCGTCA)\".\nNucleotide BLAST of GTGGATGCCTTTCGCGTCA confirmed targeting of AP2M1" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1020" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

<http://identifiers.org/rgd/620135>
